what do i do im pregnant and things arent going well with me and my boyfriend his mother wants me to have an abortion but i cant neither one of us can afford a baby i dont have insurance and his insurance will only cover the baby being born what do i do its not that we dont want the baby or we wont love it we want the baby just cant afford it oh sweetie i feel for you i've been there myself was with my boyfriend for years when i got pregnant and his mother said the same thing i told her to off she was pretty ticked with me and sent her other son to come and move' my boyfriend back home we were living together this was at months pregnant i was left with nothing after paying my rent i had a grand total of for the month i was and going to school no job no one going to hire a pregnant chick' pretty cold i felt lower than ever before not to mention 'lost' 'alone' and so on but i wasn't about to give up my baby there were a lot of tough times but he's now and has sisters and i don't regret any of it for a second his dad is still not 'in the picture' nor are his grandparents their loss i've got a great kid when i think back to the 'lowest' days when i never thought i'd 'make it through' i now wonder what was i thinking i don't know why i ever 'wasted' my time and my tears because of 'selfish losers' i don't want you to think i'm telling you to do the same just to follow your heart having a baby is serious it's a big huge 'life altering' decision do what you feel is the right thing you're the one carrying the baby p s i don't know where you live or what 'options' are available to you but i had to go on mother's allowance government funds for a while which also made the boyfriends parents whom are rich cringe oh well yoiu've gotta do what you've gotta do we 'got through it' live goes on good luck Knots Landing EastEnders Friends Humphrey Bogart One Tree Hill (TV series) The McGuire Sisters Everwood Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Atomic Kitten Similarities between the Bible and 